general_info:
With a passion for helping each client enhance their own natural beauty through state-of-the-art techniques and personalized skin care, Elaine Phuah, DO, MBA, FACOI, of Hanami Medspa practices the philosophy that aesthetics begins with optimal inner health. As a board-certified physician serving men and women in Fort Worth, Texas, and the surrounding communities, Dr. Phuah provides confidence-building, results-oriented aesthetics and medical spa treatments in a warm, welcoming environment.  
 
Licensed by the state of Texas, Dr. Phuah began her medical career at the University of Texas, Austin, where she earned her bachelor’s degree in clinical laboratory science. She went on to medical school at Kansas City University of Medicine and Biosciences, Kansas City, Missouri, where she earned a dual degree in osteopathic medicine and a masters of business administration. After earning her advanced degrees, Dr. Phuah returned to Texas to complete her residency in internal medicine and her board certification. 
 
Dr. Phuah completed additional medical training with the American Academy of Aesthetic Medicine (AAAM) and became a diplomat of AAAM. She then opened her Fort Worth, Texas, practice, Hanami Medspa, named after “cherry blossoming” in Japan.  
 
At her boutique medspa, Dr. Phuah performs all injectables herself and oversees all other aesthetics services. She spends time with every patient to understand individual health needs and skin care goals, and is available for follow-up consultations or any other concern. It’s Dr. Phuah’s mission to help men and women look and feel their best through excellent internal health and aesthetic wellness.

ABOUT US 
Since its founding in 2014, Med Physique Center For Aesthetics has provided unparalleled, innovative services to clients in Austin, Texas. Medical director Thomas Falvey, MD, and the expert team established the medspa practice as a pioneer in treatments that reverse the effects of natural aging, due to environmental factors, stress, and disease.  
The main goal of the friendly staff is to rebalance and rejuvenate the whole person in a comfortable, supportive environment through aesthetic and wellness advancements, and customized programs. To fulfill this goal, the team offers minimally-invasive anti-aging services, including Belotero Balance® and Radiesse® dermal fillers, Botox®, Dysport®, Juvéderm, IPL photo facials, Plasma fibroblast therapy, Aquagold facials, and EuroThread thread lifts. The practice also harnesses the healing powers of platelet-rich plasma (PRP) for PRP facials, PRP facelifts, and even hair regrowth. 
The compassionate staff combines state-of-the-art equipment with the highest quality products to help clients look and feel their very best. Patients also have access to exceptional skin care products to maintain the results of their treatments in between sessions. 
To find out more about Med Physique Center For Aesthetics’ personalized wellness programs, call today or book an appointment online.

general_info:
Early Diagnosis and Treatment are important to eye care. 
Optometry is the diagnosis and treatment of disease, optical deficiencies and deformities, and visual and muscular irregularities as related to the human eye and adjacent tissue. 
 
Optometrists are independent primary health care providers who examine, diagnose, treat and manage diseases and disorders of the visual system. 
 
Optometrists perform the following: 
Prescribe, provide, adapt, and fit corrective lenses, contact lenses, and low-vision rehabilitative devices  
Prescribe such things as prism lenses and eye exercises to correct eye-muscle imbalances  
Prescribe or administer drugs for the treatment of eye conditions (with additional State certification)  
Eye pain, redness, blurred vision, and complaints such as headaches or eyestrain after visual tasks are common reasons individuals seek the services of an optometrist.

general_info: Elite Athletic Therapy Physical Therapy - Austin Texas -  Sport and Orthopaedic Specialists Many people are not able to utilize physical therapy in Austin due to work obligations, time constraints, insurance restrictions and other issues. Others prefer a more discrete and convenient option.  Elite Athletic Therapy is pleased to offer boutique sports physical therapy services at your home, office or with a cooperating fitness facility. Elite athletes expect expert care in an individualized, one-on-one delivery method and you should settle for nothing less.  By eliminating the need to share your Physical Therapist with other patients in a clinic setting you will get the attention you deserve.  Help yourself improve function, decrease pain and enhance overall health and wellness. E.A.T. is pleased to offer comprehensive treatment and advanced manual techniques such as instrument assisted soft tissue mobilization, vacuum therapy and dry needling in Austin Texas. Cullen Nigrini is Austin's first Physical Therapist to obtain board certification in both Sport and Orthopaedic Physical Therapy through the American Board of Physical Therapy Specialists.   He is a certified and licensed Athletic Trainer working with elite athletes since 1999.  Nigrini has worked directly as a Physical Therapist and or an Athletic Trainer NCAA, NBA and NFL.  He also holds several advanced certifications and draws from experience with elite athletes separating Elite Athletic Therapy  from the pack. Please do not accept pain or inability to compete in your sport or hobby as the new normal. A clear and direct wellness plan that can be followed with ease is key to good health throughout life. Make Elite Athletic Therapy your choice to not only return to your active lifestyle but to thrive in doing so. Following a medical evaluation of a sport or orthopaedic injury, we believe that physical therapy is the cornerstone of any comprehensive and holistic rehabilitation program.   There is much more to health restoration then a standardized treatment plan. Each injury is as unique as the individual and requires specialized care. Our goal is to provide the best physical therapy experience in Austin. Using biomechanical assessment, exercise prescription and specialty manual interventions we can help patients restore their mind-body-health connection.

general_info: The 14 Most Important Days After a Florida Car Accident: if you or a loved one is involved in an automobile accident, you must seek medical treatment within fourteen (14) days or you get NONE of the car accident insurance you paid for. Florida's No-Fault law's changes became effective on January 1st. The law now states that if a person injured in a car accident waits to see if his or her injuries will improve and fails to seek medical care within two weeks of the accident, the person's the person's insurance carrier does not have to pay for any medical treatment or lost wages even though the person paid for this coverage. If you or someone you know is involved in a car accident, they must see a doctor right away. Waiting too long will eliminate your rights under your car insurance contract. Drive safely and watch out for those who don't. Now, if you are injured in a car accident, see a doctor right away.
